09/09/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Dragan Covic, leader of the largest Croat party in BiH, HDZ, says he is certain that BiH political leaders with seal a police reform agreement within ten days. 
Speaking on Friday (September 7th), he insisted that the latest proposal by High Representative Miroslav Lajcak is acceptable and said it is time for the country to move past this issue and focus on other important tasks.
In other news, the BiH House of Representatives approved a law that re-introduces a 40% import duty on milk and milk products, as well as meat and meat products, from Croatia and Serbia. 
The move came only a day after parliament ratified the Central European Free Trade Agreement. 
(RTRS, NTV Hayat - 07/09/07)
